    "subtype": "weapon",
    "text": "Developed by a half-orc inventor from Alkenstar who brought the technology north to battle the Whispering Tyrant alongside the orc hordes of Belkzen, the barricade buster features eight barrels fixed around a central pivot attached to a handle and firing mechanism. A barricade buster fires spheres of metal with extreme velocity and very little accuracy.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 159,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "uncommon"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Uncommon",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 409,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "09b831753bf44bcef2c3a6a7a3c6f360",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "tripod",
            "aonid": 1207,
            "game-obj": "Equipment",
            "name": "tripod",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Kickback",
        "sources": [
          {
            "link": {
              "alt": "NPC Core pg. 50",
              "aonid": 236,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "NPC Core pg. 50",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "NPC Core",
            "page": 50,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A kickback weapon is extra powerful and difficult to use due to its high recoil. A kickback weapon deals 1 additional damage with all attacks. Firing a kickback weapon gives a \u20132 circumstance penalty to the attack roll, but characters with +2 or more Strength ignore the penalty. Attaching a kickback weapon to a deployed bipod, tripod, or other stabilizer can lower or negate this penalty.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 124,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "02817d607951af1f170603a940ef5b84",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Orc",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 459",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 459",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 459,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A creature with this trait is a member of the orc ancestry. These green-skinned people tend to have darkvision. An ability with this trait can be used or selected only by orcs. An item with this trait is created and used by orcs.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 488,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "1e43c7605c9909b20b487f7dd05b5cee",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "shields",
            "href": "Shields.aspx",
            "name": "shields",
            "type": "link"
          },
          {
            "alt": "animated objects",
            "aonid": 360,
            "game-obj": "MonsterFamilies",
            "name": "animated objects",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Razing",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "1.1",
              "aonid": 227,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "1.1",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
              "aonid": 227,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core 2",
            "page": 274,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Razing weapons are particularly good at damaging objects, structures, and vehicles. Whenever you deal damage to an object (including shields and animated objects), structure, or vehicle with a razing weapon, the object takes an amount of additional damage equal to double the number of weapon damage dice.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "0a13792b093689deee7e02e0aa150254",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Repeating",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 191,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Treasure Vault pg. 221",
              "aonid": 191,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Treasure Vault pg. 221",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Treasure Vault",
            "page": 221,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A repeating weapon is a type of ranged weapon with a shorter reload time. These weapons can't be loaded with individual bolts or bullets like other crossbows and firearms; instead, they require a magazine of specialized ammunition to be loaded into a special slot. Once that magazine is in place, the ammunition is automatically loaded each time the weapon is cocked to fire, reducing its reload to the value in its reload entry (typically 0). When the ammunition runs out, a new magazine must be loaded, which requires a free hand and 3 Interact actions (to remove the old magazine, retrieve the new magazine, and slot the new magazine in place). These actions don't need to be consecutive and are the same as Interacting to reload.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 201,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "ea2a97c7c225653dc2f8c20abc1815aa",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Volley",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 283",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 283",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 283,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "This ranged weapon is less effective at close distances. Your attacks against targets that are at a distance within the range listed take a \u20132 penalty.",
        "type": "trait",
        "value": "20 ft."
      }
    ],
    "type": "stat_block"
  },
  "type": "weapon"
